body:

<p class="no-print" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#998763;">To save as PDF, use your browser's print function (Ctrl+P / Cmd+P).</p>

Usak, Turkey (GMT+3) · mirat.bayrak@gmail.com · +90 506 678 85 05 · [github.com/miratcan](https://github.com/miratcan) · [linkedin.com/in/mirat-can-bayrak](https://www.linkedin.com/in/mirat-can-bayrak)

## Summary
- Generalist engineer who has shipped Android apps, desktop tools, Django backends, React frontends, and Solidity smart contracts across 15+ years.
- Comfortable owning anything from database to deploy. Led a dev team at a global travel SaaS.
- Remote-first since 2011.

## Professional Experience

### **Valocom (BBrain)**
**Full-Stack Developer & Migration Architect**
*August 2025 – April 2026 | Remote*
- Designed an AI-orchestrated migration workflow with specialized agent roles (Explorer, Contract-Writer, Technical-Writer, Developer) to systematically migrate legacy PHP endpoints to FastAPI with zero downtime.
- Implemented core backend features: sync_tablet endpoint (13+ data dependencies), Twilio video calling, Pushy push notifications, Nettie calendar integration, license activation flows, and WooCommerce webhook processing.
- Refactored the Android tablet app: extracted components from a monolithic MainActivity, added JaCoCo test coverage, fixed 33 lint errors, and integrated external video calling (Vicasa).
- Migrated all foreign keys from integer to UUID across the database schema with backward compatibility.

### **INOHOM Smart Home Systems**
**Full Stack Developer**
*August 2023 – August 2025 | Remote*
- Built a field service management platform from scratch for HQ, distributors, and end users — covering fault reporting, job dispatch, spare part tracking, and device backups.
- Designed a multi-tier workflow: customer reports route to regional distributor, get queued for field service, and track through resolution with full audit trail.
- Backend in Django + FastAPI with Django Filters; React + Chakra UI frontend with separate portals for customers and distributors.

### **Metaverse INC.**
**Blockchain & Full Stack Developer**
*April 2022 – August 2023 | Remote*
- Built multi-chain NFT marketplace features, including Solidity contracts and Python event-processing services.
- Modernised a legacy ReactJS front-end, adding Next.js REST APIs and tooling for faster product iterations.

### **Radity**
**Software Architect**
*March 2021 – March 2022 | Remote*
- Led architecture decisions for enterprise client projects, from solution design to database migrations.
- Produced technical specs and onboarding material to keep mixed skill-level teams aligned on delivery.

### **Metglobal DMG**
**Python Developer → Development Manager**
*August 2017 – January 2021 | Istanbul, Turkey*
- Promoted to manage the Python division responsible for hotel booking engines used worldwide.
- Managed 3 teams (12 engineers total), coordinated hiring, mentoring, and delivery processes.
- Built the Cosmos static hotel data service (500K+ hotels, 232 countries) and internal dashboards using Numba, Celery, and PostgreSQL.

### **Netagenda AG**
**Backend Developer**
*July 2015 – September 2016 | Istanbul*
- Developed the backend for a Swiss marketplace platform for booking and comparing services.
- Transitioned to QA, building manual test processes and automating frontend tests with Selenium and Cucumber.

### **Reachpod**
**Software Developer**
*October 2014 – June 2015 | Istanbul*
- Built the backend for a social media management platform — unified dashboard for Facebook, Instagram, and Twitter accounts.
- Integrated multiple social media APIs for scheduling, analytics, and cross-platform posting.

### **Markafoni**
**Software Developer**
*May 2013 – September 2014 | Istanbul*
- Maintained the backend of Markafoni.com — a high-traffic e-commerce platform with 20M unique visitors and 340M page views per month.
- Worked with Celery, RabbitMQ, Redis, and MongoDB for distributed task processing at scale.
- Built a "Payment Test Server" that simulated virtual POS and payment provider APIs for integration testing.

### **Buzul Teknoloji**
**Software Engineer**
*January 2012 – July 2013 | Istanbul*
- Maintained ValMod, a Django application used by the UK government to validate hospital receipts across 5 regions in England.

### **Opsinova Multimedia & Entertainment**
**Freelance Software Developer**
*2011 – 2013 | Remote (Barcelona)*
- Built lookremix.com end-to-end: Django backend and a browser-based image processing tool with JavaScript and Backbone.js.

### **Mobil8 Solutions Limited**
**Assistant Software Programmer**
*September 2007 – February 2009 | Part-time, Turkey*
- Automated image editing and content delivery workflows using Python, replacing manual graphic production processes.

## Side Projects (solo, built and shipped)
- **[Resmin](https://github.com/miratcan/Resmin):** Visual Q&A platform where users answer questions with image stories — Django, full user/content system.
- **[TahtLang](https://github.com/tahtlang/tahtlang):** A DSL for Reigns-style card games with Tree-sitter grammar, LSP server, and balance simulator.
- **[Simsar MCP](https://simsar.trade/):** MCP server providing cryptocurrency market data to Claude and other AI assistants.
- **[Eleman](https://github.com/miratcan/Eleman):** Job board platform — FastAPI backend, React frontend, Airtable integration, Dockerised deployment.
- **[VPix](https://mirat.dev/vpix2/):** Vim-like pixel art editor in the browser. React, TypeScript, Canvas API.
- **[kaydet](https://github.com/miratcan/kaydet):** CLI journaling tool for daily notes — Python, published on PyPI.

## Education
- **Maltepe University** — B.A. Visual Communication Design (2008 – 2012)

## Skills
- **Spoken Languages:** English (C1 Advanced), Turkish (Native)
- **Technologies:** Python (Django, FastAPI), JavaScript (ReactJS, NextJS), Java (Android), Solidity, Web3, REST APIs, Celery, Redis, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Docker, Git, Linux, Nginx, Caddy, VPS deployment, Twilio, MCP, Tree-sitter
- **Core Competencies:** Backend architecture, clean code & reviews, testing strategy, performance optimisation, cross-functional collaboration, mentoring
- **Soft Skills:** Empathetic leadership, focus under pressure, async-first communication, technical mentorship, resilience training (certified, 2024)

## References
- **Carlos Galvizu** — Polarix · [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/carlos-galvizu-6659a86/) · cgalvizu@polarix.com

